com.jayway.restassured.module.mockmvc.response

Interface MockMvcResponse

  • All Superinterfaces:
    ResponseBody<MockMvcResponse>, ResponseBodyData, ResponseBodyExtractionOptions, ResponseOptions<MockMvcResponse>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    MockMvcRestAssuredResponseImpl

    public interface MockMvcResponse
extends ResponseBody<MockMvcResponse>, ResponseOptions<MockMvcResponse>
    The response of a request made by REST Assured Mock MVC.

    Usage example: 

     Response response = get("/lotto");
 String body = response.getBody().asString();
 String headerValue = response.getHeader("headerName");
 String cookieValue = response.getCookie("cookieName");

    You can also map the response body to a Java object automatically. REST Assured will use Jackson, Gson and JAXB to accommodate this: 

     Message message = get("/message").as(Message.class);

        ValidatableMockMvcResponse then()
        Returns a validatable response that's lets you validate the response. Usage example: 

         given().
         param("firstName", "John").
         param("lastName", "Doe").
 when().
         get("/greet").
 then().
         body("greeting", equalTo("John Doe"));
